**Data.** The reproduction reuses none of the source run's data. Every hypothesis is instead tested on *independent* products — each varying at least one axis (instrument, inventory, or method) from the source.{% if ctx.primary_dataset %}{% set head = (ctx.primary_dataset.definition|clean).split('. ')[0] %} The largest is {{ (head[0]|lower) ~ head[1:] }}.{% endif %}{% if ctx.datasets %} All {{ ctx.datasets|length }} dataset{{ '' if ctx.datasets|length == 1 else 's' }}, their sources, and the independence axis each varies are catalogued in the [datasets table](#sec-datasets-table) and detailed in the [appendix](#sec-datasets).{% endif %}

**Agents.** The investigation ran a fixed pipeline of Asta agents (summarized above).{% if 'AutoDiscovery' in ctx.agents_used %} Asta's **AutoDiscovery** proposed candidate relationships and ranked them by a surprise signal.{% endif %}{% if 'DataVoyager' in ctx.agents_used %} Each prespecified statistical test was executed by Asta's **DataVoyager**, an automated analysis agent.{% endif %}{% if 'Theorizer' in ctx.agents_used %} Theories were generated by Asta's literature-grounded **Theorizer** under accuracy- and novelty-focused objectives.{% endif %}{% if 'Paper Finder' in ctx.agents_used %} Source publications were located with Asta's **Paper Finder** over Semantic Scholar.{% endif %}

**Reproduction protocol.** For every candidate hypothesis we committed a prespecified test — statistic, decision metric, and success threshold — *before* analysis, re-ran it on the independent dataset, and challenged the result with a negative-control audit (the predictor shuffled, or an equivalent) before the verdict stood. Verdicts are two-axis: an *outcome* (held / partial / failed / n-a) crossed with *testability* (tested / proxy-only / untestable).

**Theory triage.** Generated theories were triaged for testability against the data in hand; each theory the data can decide was committed to a prespecified, runnable test recorded for follow-up. Running those tests is out of scope for this flow.
